rComments: Her exam questions are ridiculously specific, like a random statistic that she mentioned briefly in lecture. She says understanding the main idea is more important, but her tests do not reflect this. Also TAs are all on different pages about marking criteria. One TA will tell you one thing, but the TA who marks your work will mark you differently.

rComments: She is honestly one of the best profs i have had! i had her as a TA for HLTA02 before and she was so helpful and approachable. she did go off track a lot while giving examples but it was interesting and memorable.

Her name is actually spelled Ghazal Fazli! She's an amazing and approachable prof! I never even bothered reading the textbook in this course only because she sticked to her word and said that you didn't need to read the textbook! Her slides touched upon the textbook content which is so convenient! The exams are doable if you study the slides!

this prof is amazing and she makes sure ALL her students understand the content! the exams are not hard because she focuses on things she focuses a lot on in lectures so its easy to get a good mark as long as you goto the lecs and pay attention!
this was such an interesting and easy course!! the prof is very easy going and her lectures are fun and she makes sure to explain concepts clearly! the exams are straight forward, no surprises!

Ghazal is the best person I know, she is so understanding and funny, and makes lecture very entertaining with her witty jokes and her enthusiasm and positivity. In terms of difficulty, she is a fair professor and does not want to make your undergrad miserable, she wants you to succeed. You wont be let down.

Ghazal is really nice and approachable. She is very into everything she says, never does she act bored with a concept. Her exams are very straightforward which I appreciate very much, she gives you all the content in lectures to study from. However she had an assignment worth 30% of the grade ( more than the midterm) so you need to do well here.
